tp://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101717643011963><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>RE: Advice/Opinion on SK Race</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id= >lunaticfringesk</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>128 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Mar 26th 4:04 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.73]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It is interesting that you say that SKs are not great damage dealers, as I&amp;#8217;m sure many would disagree with you.&nbsp;&nbsp;Some might argue that the reason WAR will out-damage a SK is mostly due to duel wield, which probably makes reasonable sense.  It does, however, ignore some other things that SKs have at their disposal that increase their damage output.  An argument might sound like this:<br><br>Firstly, and probably most obvious, SK spells help increase the damage output of an SK.  Granted, they are feeble compared to a NEC of similar level, but they still add up nicely.  Heart Flutter (up to 145 pts), Heat Blood (up to 170 pts), Dooming Darkness (up to 300 pts), Boil Blood (up to 500 pts)&amp;#8212;DoTs like these sure do increase damage output of an SK, especially over a &amp;#8220;longer&amp;#8221; battle.  Further, add in the fact that an SK gets a pet, damage output is increased even more.  Malignant Bones (52SK pet) hits for up to 39 &amp; Cackling Bones (level 58 pet) hits for up to 47.  Granted, these are high level SK pets, but they illustrate an important point&amp;#8212;pets will increase the damage output of an SK, regardless of how weak they are.<br><br>Additionally, SKs seem to get much better 1H weapons than WAR (not 2HS weapons, but if the WAR is using a 2H weapon, his advantage of duel wield is gone).  I have received so many tells from WAR friends asking if my 1HB (Ebon mace) is usable by WAR, it&amp;#8217;s almost funny.  When a WAR is duel wielding, on average, I have seldom, if ever, seen them hit harder than I do as an SK&amp;#8212;their weapons just don&amp;#8217;t stack up at all.  They just seem to hit VERY FAST, not very hard (e.g. obviously there are exceptions---most WAR I know duel wield, but a very good friend of mine has a Axe of the Kromdex Kings and wields that, which almost all WAR probably would if they had that&amp;#8212;it is truly an uber weapon (2hs) &amp; he hits pretty damn hard with it&amp;#8230;.  =)    )  <br><br>For instance, a Jade Mace or lammy are very popular with WAR.  Their stats, however, are far from envious&amp;#8212;18dly, 9 dmg. &amp; 19 dly., 9 dmg. are NOT that stellar.  Ebon, on the other hand, has 24 dly, 19 dmg, which is vastly superior to either of those weapons (not factoring in the buffs from lammy). What separate the WAR from the SK is that the WAR can wield, say 2 lammys at once, while an SK can only wield 1 weapon at a time&amp;#8212;that&amp;#8217;s the big difference.  If an Ebon Mace was usable by WAR, the price of an Ebon would be astronomical.  If you doubt my veracity, do your own research&amp;#8212;the best 1HB &amp; 1HS weapons in the game are not usable by WAR, but quite a few of them are usable by SK.<br><br>Also, SKs, if they are wielding a 1H weapon, can also wield a shield, which helps to inc their stats, ac &amp; they can bash with it.  Granted, bashing doesn&amp;#8217;t do a ton of damage, but it still does damage &amp; it also interrupts.<br><br>Personally, I feel very confident that an SK can approach/surpass a WAR in the damage department if he really wants to, especially over a longer fight.  When referring to damage output only, duel wield seems to be the main advantage that WAR have over SK, but an SK can offset that advantage via spells, pets, bashing and, perhaps, better weapons.  The primary advantage of a WAR overall, to me at least, is the fact that there is no class in the game that can take the punishment that a WAR can&amp;#8212;therein lies their greatest attribute&amp;#8230;.<br><br>One more thing&amp;#8212;be careful who you select to single out in your comment about flaming.  When attacked, most people attack back.  Perhaps I am not an exception.<br><br>Lunatic<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
